    "content": "## How It Works\n\n<Table>\n  <Table.Header>\n    <Table.Row>\n      <Table.Head>Component</Table.Head>\n      <Table.Head>Role</Table.Head>\n    </Table.Row>\n  </Table.Header>\n  <Table.Body>\n    <Table.Row>\n      <Table.Cell className=\"font-medium\">MCP Server</Table.Cell>\n      <Table.Cell>Discovers plugins, registers their tools, and dispatches tool calls to the Chrome extension via WebSocket. Runs on localhost:9515 by default.</Table.Cell>\n    </Table.Row>\n    <Table.Row>\n      <Table.Cell className=\"font-medium\">Chrome Extension</Table.Cell>\n      <Table.Cell>Injects plugin adapters into matching tabs and executes tool calls in the page's MAIN world — with full access to DOM, cookies, and localStorage.</Table.Cell>\n    </Table.Row>\n    <Table.Row>\n      <Table.Cell className=\"font-medium\">Plugin SDK</Table.Cell>\n      <Table.Cell>Provides the OpenTabsPlugin base class and defineTool factory. The CLI bundles plugins into injectable adapters.</Table.Cell>\n    </Table.Row>\n  </Table.Body>\n</Table>\n\n## Tool Call Flow\n\n1. AI agent sends a tool call via MCP to `/mcp`\n2. Server validates input and dispatches via WebSocket to the extension\n3. Extension finds the best matching tab by URL pattern and ranking\n4. Extension runs the adapter's `handle()` function in the page's MAIN world\n5. Result flows back through the same chain to the AI agent\n\n## Key Features\n\n- **Zero-configuration access** — uses your existing browser sessions. No API keys, no OAuth, no service accounts.\n- **Plugin-based architecture** — anyone can create and publish OpenTabs plugins as standalone npm packages.\n- **Tab state machine** — each plugin tracks three states: closed (no matching tab), unavailable (tab exists but not ready), and ready.\n- **Hot reload** — the MCP server and file watchers auto-detect changes. Zero-restart development.\n- **36 built-in browser tools** — tab management, screenshots, DOM interaction, network capture, cookies, console logs, and more.\n- **Works with any MCP client** — Claude Code, Cursor, and any client that supports Streamable HTTP.\n\n## Next Steps\n\n- [Installation](/docs/install) — set up OpenTabs from scratch\n- [Architecture](/docs/concepts/architecture) — how the three components connect\n- [Plugin System](/docs/concepts/plugin-system) — how plugins are discovered and loaded\n- [Creating a Plugin](/docs/plugins/creating-a-plugin) — build your first plugin",
